{"id":"mybd-tbw","title":"Detect non-interactive stdin in doctor confirmations","description":"When bd doctor --fix or bd doctor --validate are run in non-interactive environments (e.g., CI pipelines, piped stdin), the confirmation prompts hang waiting for input that never comes. Even though --yes flag exists as a workaround, users may forget it or not know about it. Need to detect isatty() on stdin (similar to mybd-wan's gitHasUpstream() pattern) and skip prompts when running non-interactively. This follows the principle that bd commands should work seamlessly in automated contexts without requiring special flags.","design":"doctor fix/validate commands hang when stdin is piped (non-TTY) without --yes flag. Solution: Detect isatty() on stdin like gitHasUpstream() pattern. Skip prompts if !isatty(). Affected files: doctor_fix.go line 82, doctor_validate.go line 156.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"matt.wilkie@yukon.ca","created_at":"2026-02-10T16:01:44.6287463-07:00","created_by":"Matt Wilkie","updated_at":"2026-02-10T16:04:40.1170564-07:00","closed_at":"2026-02-10T16:04:40.1170564-07:00","close_reason":"Closed"}
